It looks here like you took a default order.xml and replaced the string &quot;ARCWriterProcessor&quot; with &quot;JDBCWriterProcessor&quot;, leaving the ARCWriterProcessor settings in place. That is not going to work. JDBCWriterProcessor has completely different settings.

I strongly recommend you get started with heritrix using the web UI. Start with the default configuration and change settings one at a time through the UI, running a brief test crawl after each configuration change. The UI will show you what settings are available, and it will create a valid order.xml, which you can then reference.

Since JDBCWriterProcessor is not included in the standard heritrix distribution, you will have make sure it&#39;s in your classpath, and add a line to Processor.options to make it show up in the UI. 

Noah


